Doc Spatz, seems like we posted almost simultaneouly.  What we do is move on.  If we don't, they have won. I ain't going to let that happen.<br><br>
I doubt if Lien is coming back. She had said her goodbyes as she had got what she was looking for.  However, doc, I would repost an appropriate post, and let me stress, APPROPRIATE post to ask what you want to know from her, because I also have no idea what you want from her.<br><br>
I would post the newspaper articles here regarding the cemetary situation, but I have no idea about about copyright stuff, so lets not get POV in dutch.  The last I heard today was that they located a hate group web site that spewed the same messages as found in the cemetaries. Rewards have been donated by the 442nd Reg. Combat Team, the 100th Battalion, the Military Intelligence Service, the 1399th Engineer Construction Battalion (SeaBees?), and a host of others to inlude the Masons, the Paralyzed Veterans of America and bunches more. All total the rewards offered is very impressive. I just found out that the bronze markers in the National Cemetary were salvaged, but there are many marble and stone artifacts at that cemetary and others where chemical agents are to caustic to clean this special paint used.<br><br>
I have had flashes of that scene in Schindlers List, where all the grave stones were ripped out of the Jewish cemetary to make a road leading to the gas chambers. Jesus fucken christ!
